race.comment: PURE MAC (5) will be better for his two outings this preparation in much stronger at Ascot. His numbers stack up well enough and expect the step up in trip to suit. Draws awkwardly but gets the nod in a competitive race. DANCING SPIRIT (10) finished 2L from the winner here over 1400m improving again. She's ready for the 1700m and is hard to risk the potent Pike-Durrant linkage. CARENTAN (6) just missed in the same contest and also presents fourth up. The extra distance shouldn't be an issue and he also has claims. HEAVENLY RAPTURE (9) is an improver but has a wide gate to manage. Chris Parnham is aboard today and that helps offset. Makes the finish at best.
